Simulate streaming data into Aurora tables.

Usage:
  stream
      Simulate all supported scenarios concurrently (default behavior).

  stream --scenario <name>
      Simulate a specific scenario with controlled behavior.

Flags:
  --scenario       Name of the scenario to simulate (customer, product, purchase, delivery)
                   If omitted or set to 'all', all scenarios will be executed.
  --rps            Records per second per parallel stream (default: 10)
  --duration       Total duration of simulation, e.g., 30s, 2m (default: 30s)
  --parallel       Number of goroutines per scenario (default: 1)
  --quality        Data quality level: high (default), medium, low
  --event-type     Event type: insert, update, delete, or mix (default: insert)

Examples:
  stream
  stream --scenario purchase --rps 100 --duration 1m
  stream --scenario delivery --quality low --parallel 4
